<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><law><structure><unit label="title" identifier="XXIX" order_by="29">COMMERCE AND TRADE</unit><unit label="chapter" identifier="365" order_by="365">TRADE PRACTICES </unit></structure><section_number>365.687</section_number><catch_line>Buyer's right of cancellation. </catch_line><order_by>687</order_by><text>Any buyer who purchases from a transient merchant goods with a value in excess of fifty dollars ($50), shall acquire the right of cancellation and any other rights granted to a buyer by KRS 367.420 to 367.460. </text><history>Created 1990 Ky. Acts ch. 102, sec. 1, effective July 13, 1990. </history><metadata><effective>July 13, 1990 </effective><pdf-author>ganesan_m</pdf-author><pdf-creation-date>2015-07-02</pdf-creation-date><pdf-download-date>2016-03-18 12:15:42</pdf-download-date><original-link>http://www.lrc.ky.gov/statutes/statute.aspx?id=34838</original-link></metadata><tags><tag>computer-parsed</tag><tag>unverified</tag></tags></law>